node.title: Queensland records no new community cases as border town remains on high COVID alert
node.alt: Queensland Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk provides a COVID-19 update
node.description: Queensland records no new COVID-19 cases in the community a day after it was announced three women in the southern border town of Goondiwindi had contracted the disease. Two cases have been recorded in hotel quarantine.
node.content:
["Queensland has recorded no new\u00a0community cases of COVID-19 a day after it was announced three women in the southern border town of Goondiwindi had contracted the disease.", "Two new\u00a0cases have been detected\u00a0in hotel quarantine.", "Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk said on Friday 11,850 people had been tested in the past 24 hours, including 245 at the Goondiwindi Hospital.", "Of the cases announced yesterday in the \"highly vaccinated\" community, two were not vaccinated and one had received their first dose of a vaccine.", "One case was a contact of a known cluster and was not of concern.", "The second case had been in the community for five days but all of their household contacts had tested negative.\u00a0", "The third case was in the community for four days and had one dose of the AstraZeneca vaccine.", "Officials\u00a0said\u00a0all of those\u00a0cases were linked to a known cluster in Moree, across the southern border in\u00a0NSW, with Acting Chief Health Officer Peter Aitken saying they\u00a0may have been linked to a NSW woman who had been in Goondiwindi for one day to do \"essential shopping\".", "Following the outbreak, residents from Moree were\u00a0restricted from crossing the Queensland border from early today.", "Additional restrictions will be placed on residents in the\u00a0NSW region for the next seven days, including no visitors to aged care and hospitals.", "At least 90.9 people aged over 15 in the Goondiwindi Regional Council area have received two doses of a COVID-19 vaccine.", "Ms Palaszczuk said 78.81 per cent of Queenslanders aged over 16 have received their first dose of the vaccine, with 65.81 per cent now having had both.", "Queensland Health has also revealed viral fragments of COVID-19 have also been detected in sewage during routine testing at Cairns'\u00a0northern beaches this week.", "The Premier said she had been impressed by the number of tests in Goondiwindi.\u00a0", "\"Overnight Moree was removed from our border bubble\u2026 there are 33 cases in Moree and there could be even more announced today,\" she said.", "\"What we do know is that a large proportion of people who are being tested positive are unvaccinated, so that's a concern and that's in addition to the three cases that were reported in Queensland yesterday,\" she said.", "More to come.", "", "
Outbreak: How Australia lost control of the Delta variant
"]
